sub_title: International Media Management | Creative Producing and Content Creation
summary:
My name is Boyana Tosheva and I am currently in my 3rd year of Breda University of Applied Sciences.
In my three years at BUas, I got the chance to explore different media fields and figure out which one I prefer and what kind of roles I am good at. It was confirmed that my passion lies in Filmmaking. 
The way I see it, nowadays to reach people most efficiently and effectively, you need to present your message/story/etc. where they would go to watch/read/hear it – in my opinion, the best channel for that is an AV production. Moreover, not only can you reach a lot of people at the same time, but you also can give voice to subjects that are being muted or even your own. Art does not need to have a meaning but it always does – be it for the creator or the viewer.

While working on AV productions like short movies, music videos, internal marketing campaigns etc., I got to try our different crew positions. I discovered that my skills are best utilized in the positions of Producer and Director. My strongest skills are in the organization, management and creative content development
